        "Do not assume regulated items follow the same rules across state lines": "莫假设受监管物品在跨州时遵循相同规则",
        "Do not assume rules from your origin state apply. Rules vary across state, local, and federal jurisdictions. Verify directly with official sources.": "莫假设出发州个规则同样适用。州、地方搭联邦各司法管辖区个规则不一样。请直接向官方来源核实。",
        "Do not characterize voter registration by non-citizens using legal-conclusion or accusatory language. Use neutral framing such as 'generally not eligible' and 'may create immigration complications'. Direct readers to consult a licensed immigration attorney. Do not give procedural advice for any specific state.": "请勿使用法律结论或指控性措辞描述非美国公民的选民登记。请采用中立表述,如「通常无资格」和「可能引发移民方面的复杂问题」。引导读者咨询持证移民律师。请勿就任何特定州提供程序性建议。",
        "Do not characterize whether any visa category can establish residency in a specific state as a determination. Frame as classification rules to verify with the school registrar and the state higher-education agency. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "请勿对任何签证类别能否在特定州确立居住身份作出判定式的描述。请表述为需向学校教务处及州高等教育机构核实的分类规则。请遵循 SafeCopy 的回避词表。",
        "Do not determine residency. List factors to verify. Direct to the relevant agency or school.": "请勿判定居住身份。仅列出需核实的因素。引导至相关机构或学校。",
        "Do not determine that a household 'is' or 'is not' eligible for Medicaid. Frame as items to verify with the state Medicaid agency. Use 'may apply' and 'rules differ by jurisdiction'. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "请勿判定某家庭「符合」或「不符合」Medicaid 资格。请表述为需向州 Medicaid 机构核实的事项。使用「可能适用」及「各司法管辖区的规则不同」。请遵循 SafeCopy 的回避词表。",
        "Do not list which states grant in-state tuition for DACA recipients. Frame as classification rules to verify with the school registrar and the state higher-education agency.": "请勿列出哪些州向 DACA 受益人提供本州学费。请表述为需向学校教务处及州高等教育机构核实的分类规则。",
        "Do not provide a public-charge determination or say that using benefits 'will' or 'will not' affect immigration. Frame as 'may interact' and recommend consulting a licensed immigration attorney. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "请勿作出「公共负担」(public charge)判定,亦不要陈述使用福利「将」或「不会」影响移民。请表述为「可能相互影响」,并建议咨询持证移民律师。请遵循 SafeCopy 的回避词表。",
        "Do not provide medical or transport instructions for controlled substances.": "请勿提供针对管制药品的医疗或运输操作指引。",
        "Do not provide tactical instructions for transporting, possessing, hiding, storing, modifying, or avoiding enforcement for regulated items.": "请勿提供运输、持有、藏匿、存放、改装受监管物品或规避执法的具体操作指引。",
        "Do not provide tax advice. Direct to official tax agency and qualified professionals.": "请勿提供税务建议。引导至官方税务机构及合格专业人士。",
        "Do not provide tax advice. Direct to state tax agency or qualified tax professional.": "请勿提供税务建议。引导至州税机关或合格税务专业人士。",
        "Do not say a Board of Nursing in a particular state grants or refuses an applicant's NCLEX path. Use 'verify with the destination Board of Nursing'. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "请勿陈述某州护理委员会是否批准或拒绝申请人的 NCLEX 路径。请使用「向目的地州护理委员会核实」。请遵循 SafeCopy 的回避词表。",
        "Do not say a particular aid program 'is open to' or 'is closed to' DACA recipients or LPRs. Use 'verify with the state aid agency and the school financial-aid office'. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "请勿陈述某助学项目对 DACA 受益人或 LPR 是「开放」或「不开放」。请使用「向州助学机构及学校助学金办公室核实」。请遵循 SafeCopy 的回避词表。",
        "Do not say a person 'can' or 'cannot' enroll. Use 'verify current eligibility categories with the marketplace operator' since federal rules have changed. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "请勿陈述某人「可以」或「不可以」投保。由于联邦规则曾发生变化,请使用「向市场运营方核实当前的资格类别」。请遵循 SafeCopy 的回避词表。",
        "Do not state how a specific state defines residency for a given visa category or that someone 'is' a resident. Frame as 'rules differ by jurisdiction' and 'verify with the destination-state tax agency'. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "请勿陈述特定州如何对某签证类别定义居住身份,或某人「是」居民。请表述为「各司法管辖区的规则不同」及「向目的地州税务机关核实」。请遵循 SafeCopy 的回避词表。",
        "Do not state how a specific state defines residency or that someone 'is' a resident. Frame as 'rules differ by jurisdiction' and 'verify with the destination-state tax agency'. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "请勿陈述特定州如何定义居住身份,或某人「是」居民。请表述为「各司法管辖区的规则不同」及「向目的地州税务机关核实」。请遵循 SafeCopy 的回避词表。",
        "Do not state that any specific board does or does not license a given visa category. Frame everything as items to verify with the destination-state board. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "请勿陈述任何具体委员会是否向特定签证类别核发执照。所有内容均应表述为需向目的地州委员会核实的事项。请遵循 SafeCopy 的回避词表。",
        "Do not state that any specific board does or does not license non-citizens. Frame everything as items to verify with the destination-state board. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "请勿陈述任何具体委员会是否向非美国公民核发执照。所有内容均应表述为需向目的地州委员会核实的事项。请遵循 SafeCopy 的回避词表。",
        "Do not state that any specific person is or is not required to register. Frame as a federal requirement that 'may apply' depending on age and sex, with state implementation details to verify. Use neutral language and follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "请勿陈述任何具体人士是否必须登记。请表述为依据年龄与性别「可能适用」的联邦要求,具体由各州实施,需要核实。请使用中立措辞并遵循 SafeCopy 的回避词表。",
        "Do not state whether the user is eligible for licensure. Only identify requirements to verify.": "请勿陈述用户是否具备执照资格。仅列出需核实的要求。",
        "Do not state which states do or do not issue licenses to a given group, and do not list specific accepted documents. Frame everything as items to verify with the destination-state DMV.": "请勿陈述哪些州向某一群体核发或不核发驾照,也不要列出具体接受的文件。所有内容均应表述为需向目的地州 DMV 核实的事项。",
        "Do not state which states issue or do not issue licenses to a given visa category, and do not list specific accepted documents. Frame everything as items to verify with the destination-state DMV. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "请勿陈述哪些州向特定签证类别核发或不核发驾照,也不要列出具体接受的文件。所有内容均应表述为需向目的地州 DMV 核实的事项。请遵循 SafeCopy 的回避词表。",
        "Document lists accepted by state DMVs for non-citizen license or state-ID applicants can differ from those accepted for U.S. citizens, and accepted combinations may vary by jurisdiction.": "各州 DMV 对非美国公民驾照或州身份证申请人接受的文件清单,可能与对美国公民接受的清单不同,且接受的组合方式可能因司法管辖区而异。",
        "Documents for proof of identity": "身份证明所需文件",
        "Done": "完成",
        "Driver's license": "驾驶执照",
        "Driving across one or more state lines for travel.": "为出行而开车跨过一个或者多个州界。",
        "Driving with coverage that does not meet destination-state minimums can create compliance and financial problems.": "若保额未达到目的地州的最低要求即上路,可能造成合规及财务问题。",
        "Drug screen requirements": "药检要求",
        "Edit selections": "编辑选择",
        "Emissions testing requirement": "排放检测要求",
        "Employer policy": "雇主政策",
        "Employment Authorization": "工作授权",
        "Employment paperwork": "就业相关文件",
        "Endorsement requirements if already licensed": "若已持有执照,所适用的背书要求",
        "Endorsement, reciprocity, temporary permits, and continuing education requirements vary by state and profession.": "背书、互认、临时许可及继续教育要求因州和职业而异。",
        "Endorsement, reciprocity, temporary practice, and continuing education.": "背书、互认、临时执业及继续教育。",
        "Enhanced or REAL ID": "Enhanced 或 REAL ID",
        "Establishing a new permanent residence in the destination state.": "在目的地州建立新个永久居所。",
        "Eviction and late-fee rules": "驱逐及滞纳金规则",
        "Example checklist categories": "示例清单类别",
        "Exploring options. Receive a broad overview checklist.": "了解可选方案。获取一份概览清单。",
        "F-1 OPT and STEM OPT specific. Use verify with the DSO and SEVP Portal guidance. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list (legal-conclusion phrasing and penalty-avoidance phrasing). Do not advise on a specific status outcome.": "仅适用于 F-1 OPT 与 STEM OPT。请使用「向 DSO 与 SEVP Portal 指引核实」。请避免使用 iOS SafeCopy 回避词表中的法律结论性措辞及规避处罚类措辞。请勿就具体身份结果提供建议。",
        "F-1 specific. Frame as verify with both DSOs and reference Study in the States or ICE materials. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list.": "仅适用于 F-1。请表述为需向双方 DSO 核实,并参考 Study in the States 或 ICE 资料。请避免使用 iOS SafeCopy 回避词表中的措辞。",
        "F-1 students on post-completion OPT or a STEM OPT extension generally use the SEVP Portal or work with their DSO to update physical and mailing address, employer information, and other personal data, typically within 10 days of a change. Unemployment-day limits during OPT continue to apply during and after a move.": "处于完成学业后 OPT 或 STEM OPT 延期阶段的 F-1 学生,通常通过 SEVP Portal 或与 DSO 合作更新实际居住地址、邮寄地址、雇主信息及其他个人数据,一般需在变更后 10 天内完成。OPT 期间的失业天数上限在搬屋期间及之后仍然适用。",
        "F-1, J-1, M-1, and Q specific. Frame as items to verify with IRS guidance and the employer. Do not state that a particular worker is exempt from FICA. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list.": "仅适用于 F-1、J-1、M-1 与 Q。请表述为需向 IRS 指引及雇主核实的事项。请勿陈述某具体雇员可豁免 FICA。请避免使用 iOS SafeCopy 回避词表中的措辞。",
        "Factors that may affect residency for tuition, taxes, licensing, benefits.": "可能影响学费、税务、执照及福利所适用居住身份的相关因素。",
        "Failing to register on time may affect eligibility for federal benefits, federal jobs, and naturalization later, even though the requirement is federal. State DMV workflows can also trigger automatic registration, which applicants should understand before applying.": "未及时登记可能影响日后联邦福利、联邦工作及入籍的资格,尽管该要求属于联邦层面。州 DMV 流程也可能自动触发登记,申请人在申请前应予了解。",
        "Family move": "全家搬屋",
        "Federal HealthCare.gov guidance describes a list of immigration statuses considered lawfully present for purposes of the Affordable Care Act marketplace, which includes many common nonimmigrant categories. These categories can purchase coverage without a five-year waiting period that applies in many Medicaid contexts.": "联邦 HealthCare.gov 指引列出了在《平价医疗法》(ACA)市场上被视为合法居留的移民身份清单,其中包含许多常见的非移民类别。这些类别在购买保险时不适用于许多 Medicaid 情形中的五年等待期。",
        "Federal Medicaid and CHIP rules generally include a five-year waiting period for many qualified non-citizens after obtaining qualified status, with several federal exceptions. States may use an option that removes the waiting period for children and pregnant people, and some states cover certain groups with state funds.": "联邦 Medicaid 与 CHIP 规则通常对许多符合资格的非美国公民在取得资格身份后设有五年等待期,并存在若干联邦例外。各州可选择取消儿童和孕妇的等待期,某些州亦使用州级资金为特定群体提供保障。",
        "Federal Medicare guidance generally describes eligibility for non-citizens who are lawfully admitted for permanent residence and have lived in the United States for five continuous years. Federal Medicaid rules for most nonimmigrants are narrower than for LPRs, with state-specific options for emergency Medicaid and for lawfully residing children and pregnant individuals.": "联邦 Medicare 指引通常说明,合法获准取得永久居留并在美连续居住五年的非美国公民可具备资格。联邦 Medicaid 规则对多数非移民较 LPR 更为狭窄,各州在紧急 Medicaid 以及合法居留儿童和孕妇方面有各自的可选规定。",
        "Federal REAL ID rules require evidence of lawful status, and many states issue a REAL ID to nonimmigrant visa holders only with an expiration date that does not extend past the I-94, the visa, or another underlying federal document. Implementation differs between states, and standard (non-REAL-ID) options may or may not be offered.": "联邦 REAL ID 规则要求提供合法身份证明;许多州仅向非移民签证持有人核发到期日不超过 I-94、签证或其他底层联邦文件的 REAL ID。各州的实施方式不同,是否提供标准(非 REAL ID)替代方案因州而异。",
        "Federal SNAP, TANF, and similar programs apply a waiting period to many qualified non-citizens. Some states use state funds to operate replacement or supplemental programs that cover groups not eligible for the federal program, with differing rules.": "联邦 SNAP、TANF 及类似项目对许多符合资格的非美国公民设有等待期。部分州使用州资金运营替代或补充项目,为不符合联邦项目条件的群体提供保障,规则各不相同。",
        "Federal law": "联邦法律",
        "Federal law (INA section 265) generally directs non-citizens to report a change of address to USCIS within 10 days of moving, typically through Form AR-11 or the USCIS online change-of-address tool. The federal filing is separate from updating a state DMV record, an employer, a school, or the U.S. Postal Service.": "联邦法律(INA 第 265 条)通常要求非美国公民在搬屋后 10 天内向 USCIS 报告地址变更,通常通过 Form AR-11 或 USCIS 在线地址变更工具进行。该联邦申报与更新州 DMV 记录、雇主、学校或美国邮政记录无关。",
        "Federal law generally requires motor vehicle offices to offer voter registration to applicants, and forms are screened for citizenship attestations. Non-citizens generally are not eligible to register for federal elections, and a registration record can later create immigration complications.": "联邦法律通常要求车管局向申请人提供选民登记机会,表格会筛查公民身份声明。非美国公民通常无资格登记参加联邦选举,登记记录日后可能引发移民方面的复杂问题。",
        "Federal residency for tax purposes determines whether worldwide income is reported, which IRS forms apply, and how an interstate move's first and last year are filed at the federal level, separately from state residency rules.": "联邦税务居住身份决定是否申报全球收入、适用哪些 IRS 表格,以及州际搬屋所涉首末年度在联邦层面的申报方式,与州居住身份规则各自独立。",
        "Federal rules govern which immigration statuses can purchase coverage and receive financial help through the Affordable Care Act marketplace, and those rules have changed. State-based marketplaces and state-funded programs add another layer that can differ between origin and destination.": "联邦规则规定哪些移民身份可以通过《平价医疗法》(ACA)市场购买保险并获得财务援助,且这些规则曾发生变化。州级市场及州资金支持的项目又增加了一层规则,出发州与目的地州可能不同。",
        "Federal tax authority": "联邦税务机关",
        "Federal tax authority general guidance": "联邦税务机关一般指引",
        "Filing Requirements, Residency, and Telecommuting FAQs": "申报要求、居住身份与远程办公常见问题",
        "Flags risk levels so you know where to focus": "标出风险等级,好让你晓得重点关注哪里",
        "Florida Board of Governors page on residency for tuition purposes for the State University System. flbog.edu returns 403 to non-browser requests (Cloudflare); this is a known false negative.": "Florida Board of Governors 关于 State University System 学费居住身份的页面。flbog.edu 对非浏览器请求返回 403(Cloudflare);属于已知误报。",
        "Florida FLHSMV documentation page for nonimmigrant applicants for driver licenses and identification cards.": "Florida FLHSMV 关于驾照与身份证非移民申请人的文件页面。",
        "Follow device language": "跟设备语言",
        "For L-1, whether the new worksite is the same qualifying U.S. office described in the petition or a different one": "对 L-1 而言,新工作地点是否仍为申请所述的同一合资格美国办公地点",
        "For L-1A, L-1B, and O-1 status, USCIS treats a move to a new worksite as a material change in some fact patterns and not others, depending on what the original petition described and whether the new location is consistent with the approved terms. The analysis follows the underlying petition, not LCA-based MSA rules.": "对 L-1A、L-1B 与 O-1 身份,USCIS 会根据原申请的描述及新地点是否与已批准条款一致,在不同事实情形下将搬屋至新工作地点视为或不视为重大变更。该分析依据底层申请进行,而非依据基于 LCA 的 MSA 规则。",
        "For O-1, whether the new venue, event, engagement, or agent arrangement falls within the approved petition scope": "对 O-1 而言,新的场地、活动、约聘或代理安排是否在已批准申请的范围之内",
        "For federal tax purposes, a non-citizen is generally treated as a resident alien if they meet the Substantial Presence Test or hold lawful permanent resident status, with separate rules in IRS Publication 519 for exempt individuals (such as certain F-1, J-1, M-1, and Q students and scholars) whose days of presence may not count.": "在联邦税务上,非美国公民通常在满足 Substantial Presence Test 或持有合法永久居民身份的情况下被视为居民外国人;IRS Publication 519 对豁免个人(例如某些 F-1、J-1、M-1 与 Q 学生及学者)另有规定,其在美天数可能不计入。",
        "For nursing specifically, how the destination state treats primary state of residency under the Nurse Licensure Compact for a non-citizen who declares either the country of origin or the compact state, and any credentials-evaluation requirement (for example, CGFNS) for internationally educated applicants": "就护理而言,目的地州在 Nurse Licensure Compact 下如何处理非美国公民对其原籍国或 Compact 州的主要居住州声明,以及对国际教育背景申请人的学历评估要求(例如 CGFNS)",
        "Form AR-11 paper version posted on uscis.gov.": "在 uscis.gov 上发布的 Form AR-11 纸质版本。",
        "Frame AR-11 as a federal reporting step to verify, not a guarantee of status. Do not state that any specific status category is or is not covered without source. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list (legal-conclusion phrasing such as the i-word, the p-words, and penalty-avoidance phrasing). Direct readers to consult a licensed immigration attorney for status-specific guidance.": "请将 AR-11 表述为需核实的联邦报告步骤,而非身份层面的承诺。在没有来源支撑的情况下,请勿陈述任何具体身份类别是否被涵盖。请避免使用 iOS SafeCopy 回避词表中的法律结论性措辞(如 i 字、p 字相关词汇及规避处罚类措辞)。请引导读者就身份相关的指引咨询持证移民律师。",
        "Frame as a federal requirement that may apply, with a nonimmigrant exception that may apply based on continuous valid status. Do not state that any specific person is or is not required to register. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list.": "请表述为「可能适用」的联邦要求,并存在依据持续有效身份「可能适用」的非移民例外。请勿陈述任何具体人士是否必须办理登记。请避免使用 iOS SafeCopy 回避词表中的措辞。",
        "Frame as items to verify in IRS Publication 519 and with a qualified tax preparer. Do not state a person is a dual-status filer for a particular year. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list.": "请表述为需向 IRS Publication 519 及合格报税员核实的事项。请勿陈述某人在特定年度属于双重身份申报者。请避免使用 iOS SafeCopy 回避词表中的措辞。",
        "Frame as items to verify with CMS and the destination-state Medicaid agency. Federal rules have changed and may continue to change. Do not state a person is or is not eligible. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list.": "请表述为需向 CMS 及目的地州 Medicaid 机构核实的事项。联邦规则曾发生变化,且可能继续变化。请勿陈述某人是否具备资格。请避免使用 iOS SafeCopy 回避词表中的措辞。",
        "Frame as items to verify with IRS Publication 519 and a tax preparer. Do not state a person is or is not a resident alien for federal tax purposes. Use may apply and rules differ by jurisdiction. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list.": "请表述为需向 IRS Publication 519 及报税员核实的事项。请勿陈述某人在联邦税务上是否为居民外国人。请使用「可能适用」及「各司法管辖区的规则不同」。请避免使用 iOS SafeCopy 回避词表中的措辞。",
        "Frame as items to verify with the DSO or J-1 sponsor and Study in the States or ICE guidance. This item is specific to F-1, M-1, and J-1 status. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list (legal-conclusion phrasing and penalty-avoidance phrasing).": "请表述为需向 DSO 或 J-1 项目主办方,以及 Study in the States 或 ICE 指引核实的事项。本项仅适用于 F-1、M-1 与 J-1 身份。请避免使用 iOS SafeCopy 回避词表中的法律结论性措辞及规避处罚类措辞。",
        "Frame as items to verify with the current HealthCare.gov or state-based marketplace lists. Do not state any specific category is or is not on the lawfully present list, since federal rules have changed. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list.": "请表述为需向当前 HealthCare.gov 或州级市场清单核实的事项。由于联邦规则曾发生变化,请勿陈述某具体类别是否在合法居留清单上。请避免使用 iOS SafeCopy 回避词表中的措辞。",
        "Full disclaimer:": "完整免责声明:",
        "General information only. Not legal advice. Verify with official sources.": "只供一般信息参考。不构成法律建议。请向官方来源核实。",
        "General information only. Verify with the relevant official source. Not legal advice.": "只供一般信息参考。请向相关官方来源核实。不构成法律建议。",
        "Generate checklist": "生成清单",
