        "Some items may be regulated differently across state lines and may involve state law, local ordinances, federal law, or agency rules.": "部分物品在跨州时可能受到不同监管,可能涉及州法律、地方条例、联邦法律或机构规则。",
        "Some items may be regulated differently across state lines and may involve state law, local ordinances, federal law, or agency rules. MoveSafe does not determine whether possession, transportation, or use is lawful in any specific situation. Verify directly with official sources and consult a licensed attorney or relevant agency if needed.": "部分项目在跨州个时候可能受到不一样个监管,可能涉及州法律、地方条例、联邦法律或者机构规则。MoveSafe 不判定任何具体情形下个持有、运输或者使用是否合法。请直接向官方来源核实,有需要再咨询持证律师或者相关机构。",
        "Some sources have not been verified recently. Check the official website before relying on them.": "部分来源近期尚未核实。在依据这些来源前,请检查官方网站。",
        "Some states issue driver licenses or state IDs to nonimmigrant visa applicants on a shortened renewal cycle that tracks the I-94 or an underlying federal document, instead of the multi-year cycle used for citizens. Fees, renewal timing, and steps after a status extension can differ between origin and destination states.": "部分州向非移民签证申请人核发驾照或州身份证时,采用与 I-94 或底层联邦文件挂钩的较短续证周期,而非适用于公民的多年周期。费用、续证时间及身份延期后的步骤可能在出发州与目的地州之间不同。",
        "Source not yet documented": "来源尚未记录",
        "Source status: %@": "来源状态:%@",
        "Sources referenced in this checklist": "本清单引用个来源",
        "Sources to verify only": "只看要核实来源",
        "Sources:": "来源:",
        "Sources: placeholder - verify with the relevant official agency.": "来源:占位项-请向相关官方机构核实。",
        "Stale or placeholder sources only": "只看过时或占位来源",
        "Stale source": "过时来源",
        "Stale source warning": "过时来源警告",
        "Start fresh": "重新开始",
        "Starting work at a new worksite outside the LCA's MSA without an amended petition can affect status maintenance, and the timing of the amended petition filing matters for when the worker can begin at the new location.": "在未提交修正申请的情况下在 LCA 所属 MSA 之外的新工作地点开始工作,可能影响身份维持;修正申请的提交时机将影响雇员可在新地点开工的时间。",
        "State DMV document checklists for nonimmigrant visa applicants (F-1, J-1, H-1B, L-1, O-1 and similar) can differ from those used for U.S. citizens or lawful permanent residents. Accepted combinations of passport, visa, I-94, I-20 or DS-2019, and I-797 or employer letter may vary, and some states ask for an SSN card or an SSA ineligibility letter.": "州 DMV 针对非移民签证申请人(F-1、J-1、H-1B、L-1、O-1 及类似)的文件清单可能与适用于美国公民或合法永久居民的清单不同。护照、签证、I-94、I-20 或 DS-2019,以及 I-797 或雇主函件等可接受的组合方式可能不同;部分州要求 SSN 卡或 SSA 不符合资格证明信。",
        "State University of New York Board of Trustees policy on residency for tuition purposes, including which visa categories can establish New York domicile. suny.edu returns 403 to non-browser requests (Cloudflare); this is a known false negative on the long-standing state university system domain.": "State University of New York 董事会关于学费居住身份的政策,包括哪些签证类别可在 New York 确立住所。suny.edu 对非浏览器请求返回 403(Cloudflare);这是该长期存在的州立大学系统域名上的已知误报。",
        "State filing requirements, part-year residency, remote work implications.": "州申报要求、部分年度居住身份及远程工作的影响。",
        "State grant and scholarship programs each have their own rules about whether non-citizen students may be considered, what application form (FAFSA, a state alternative, or an institutional form) is used, and what documentation is needed.": "各州助学金与奖学金项目各自规定非美国公民学生是否在考量范围、使用何种申请表(FAFSA、州级替代表格或院校表格)及所需文件。",
        "State labor law basics (paid sick leave, breaks, final pay rules)": "州劳动法基本事项(带薪病假、休息时间、最终工资规则)",
        "State law": "州法律",
        "State residency basics": "州居住身份基础",
        "State tax filing can apply even when income is earned remotely. Rules differ by state.": "即便收入来自远程工作,州税申报仍可能适用。各州规则不同。",
        "State tax residency is determined under each state's own rules, which may differ from federal tax residency. A person treated as a nonresident alien on the federal return may still be a resident, part-year resident, or nonresident for state purposes depending on domicile, days of physical presence, employer location, and other factors. States may or may not conform to federal income tax treaty exclusions.": "州税居住身份依据各州自身规则认定,可能与联邦税务居住身份不同。在联邦申报上被视为非居民外国人之人,基于住所、实际居留天数、雇主所在地及其他因素,仍可能在州层面属于居民、部分年度居民或非居民。各州是否依循联邦所得税协定豁免不一。",
        "State tax residency is determined under each state's own rules, which may differ from federal tax residency. Domicile, days of physical presence, employer location, and other factors can each play a role.": "州税居住身份依据各州自身规则认定,可能与联邦税务居住身份不同。住所、实际居留天数、雇主所在地及其他因素都可能起到作用。",
        "State tax withholding, labor law basics, remote work considerations.": "州税预扣、劳动法基本事项及远程工作注意事项。",
        "States and individual public colleges and universities use different tuition-classification rules for non-citizens, including how prior in-state high school attendance, current immigration status, and a parent's residency are considered.": "各州及各公立学院和大学对非美国公民采用不同的学费分类规则,包括如何考量此前在本州的高中就读情况、当前移民身份及父母的居住身份。",
        "States may require proof of identity, residency, lawful presence, school documents, or other paperwork.": "各州可能要求提供身份证明、居住证明、合法居留证明、学校文件或其他材料。",
        "Staying in another state temporarily without intending to become a resident.": "暂时在另外一个州住,冇得打算成为该州居民。",
